{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":506,"text":"I would like to talk to you about"},{"time":2360,"text":"a very special group of animals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":4992,"text":"There are 10,000 species of birds in the world."},{"time":8993,"text":"Vultures are amongst the most threatened group of birds."},{"time":13601,"text":"When you see a vulture like this, the first thing"},{"time":16613,"text":"that comes to your mind is, these are disgusting, ugly,"},{"time":20589,"text":"greedy creatures that are just after your flesh,"},{"time":23548,"text":"associated with politicians. (Laughter) (Applause)"},{"time":30875,"text":"I want to change that perception. I want to change"},{"time":33650,"text":"those feelings you have for these birds, because"},{"time":36360,"text":"they need our sympathy. They really do. (Laughter)"},{"time":39410,"text":"And I'll tell you why."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40959,"text":"First of all, why do they have such a bad press?"},{"time":44551,"text":"When Charles Darwin went across the Atlantic in 1832"},{"time":48538,"text":"on the Beagle, he saw the turkey vulture,"},{"time":51730,"text":"and he said, \"These are disgusting birds"},{"time":54570,"text":"with bald scarlet heads that are formed to revel in putridity.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":60631,"text":"You could not get a worse insult, and that from Charles Darwin. (Laughter)"},{"time":65201,"text":"You know, he changed his mind when he came back,"},{"time":68062,"text":"and I'll tell you why."},{"time":69378,"text":"They've also be associated with Disney — (Laughter) —"},{"time":72669,"text":"personified as goofy, dumb, stupid characters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":77461,"text":"More recently, if you've been following the Kenyan press"},{"time":81037,"text":"— (Laughter) (Applause) (Cheers) —"},{"time":88156,"text":"these are the attributes that they associated"},{"time":91508,"text":"the Kenyan MPs with. But I want to challenge that."},{"time":94820,"text":"I want to challenge that. Do you know why?"},{"time":97372,"text":"Because MPs"},{"time":100092,"text":"do not keep the environment clean. (Laughter)"},{"time":104963,"text":"MPs do not help to prevent the spread of diseases."},{"time":109925,"text":"They are hardly monogamous. (Laughter) (Applause)"},{"time":116274,"text":"They are far from being extinct. (Laughter)"},{"time":120037,"text":"And, my favorite is, vultures are better looking. (Applause) (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":126938,"text":"So there's two types of vultures in this planet."},{"time":130889,"text":"There are the New World vultures that are mainly found"},{"time":133162,"text":"in the Americas, like the condors and the caracaras,"},{"time":136103,"text":"and then the Old World vultures, where we have"},{"time":138402,"text":"16 species. From these 16, 11 of them are facing"},{"time":141890,"text":"a high risk of extinction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144977,"text":"So why are vultures important? First of all,"},{"time":148394,"text":"they provide vital ecological services. They clean up."},{"time":151875,"text":"They're our natural garbage collectors."},{"time":154169,"text":"They clean up carcasses right to the bone."},{"time":156802,"text":"They help to kill all the bacteria. They help absorb anthrax"},{"time":160440,"text":"that would otherwise spread and cause"},{"time":163113,"text":"huge livestock losses and diseases in other animals."},{"time":167197,"text":"Recent studies have shown that in areas where there are"},{"time":169936,"text":"no vultures, carcasses take up to three to four times"},{"time":172939,"text":"to decompose, and this has huge ramifications"},{"time":175508,"text":"for the spread of diseases."}]},{"cues":[{"time":178403,"text":"Vultures also have tremendous historical significance."},{"time":181819,"text":"They have been associated in ancient Egyptian culture."},{"time":185063,"text":"Nekhbet was the symbol of the protector"},{"time":188163,"text":"and the motherhood, and together with the cobra,"},{"time":191251,"text":"symbolized the unity between Upper and Lower Egypt."},{"time":195365,"text":"In Hindu mythology, Jatayu was the vulture god,"},{"time":199173,"text":"and he risked his life in order to save the goddess Sita"},{"time":204445,"text":"from the 10-headed demon Ravana."},{"time":207102,"text":"In Tibetan culture, they are performing very important"},{"time":210533,"text":"sky burials. In places like Tibet, there are no places"},{"time":213245,"text":"to bury the dead, or wood to cremate them,"},{"time":216309,"text":"so these vultures provide a natural disposal system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":220497,"text":"So what is the problem with vultures?"},{"time":222964,"text":"We have eight species of vultures that occur in Kenya,"},{"time":225835,"text":"of which six are highly threatened with extinction."},{"time":229822,"text":"The reason is that they're getting poisoned, and the reason"},{"time":232441,"text":"that they're getting poisoned is because there's"},{"time":235033,"text":"human-wildlife conflicts. The pastoral communities"},{"time":237721,"text":"are using this poison to target predators,"},{"time":241073,"text":"and in return, the vultures are falling victim to this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244708,"text":"In South Asia, in countries like India and Pakistan,"},{"time":247372,"text":"four species of vultures are listed as critically endangered,"},{"time":250853,"text":"which means they have less than 10 or 15 years to go extinct,"},{"time":254204,"text":"and the reason is because they are falling prey"},{"time":257514,"text":"by consuming livestock that has been treated"},{"time":259962,"text":"with a painkilling drug like Diclofenac."},{"time":262634,"text":"This drug has now been banned for veterinary use in India,"},{"time":265731,"text":"and they have taken a stand."},{"time":268250,"text":"Because there are no vultures, there's been a spread"},{"time":270570,"text":"in the numbers of feral dogs at carcass dump sites,"},{"time":273371,"text":"and when you have feral dogs, you have a huge time bomb"},{"time":276552,"text":"of rabies. The number of cases of rabies"},{"time":279194,"text":"has increased tremendously in India."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281922,"text":"Kenya is going to have one of the largest wind farms in Africa:"},{"time":285367,"text":"353 wind turbines are going to be up at Lake Turkana."},{"time":288603,"text":"I am not against wind energy, but we need to work"},{"time":290883,"text":"with the governments, because wind turbines"},{"time":294092,"text":"do this to birds. They slice them in half."},{"time":296692,"text":"They are bird-blending machines."},{"time":299526,"text":"In West Africa, there's a horrific trade"},{"time":302204,"text":"of dead vultures to serve the witchcraft and the fetish market."}]},{"cues":[{"time":307575,"text":"So what's being done? Well, we're conducting research"},{"time":310407,"text":"on these birds. We're putting transmitters on them."},{"time":313687,"text":"We're trying to determine their basic ecology,"},{"time":316063,"text":"and see where they go."},{"time":318502,"text":"We can see that they travel different countries, so"},{"time":320543,"text":"if you focus on a problem locally, it's not going to help you."},{"time":323839,"text":"We need to work with governments in regional levels."},{"time":326546,"text":"We're working with local communities."},{"time":329482,"text":"We're talking to them about appreciating vultures,"},{"time":332624,"text":"about the need from within to appreciate these"},{"time":335179,"text":"wonderful creatures and the services that they provide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":338216,"text":"How can you help? You can become active,"},{"time":341229,"text":"make noise. You can write a letter to your government"},{"time":343952,"text":"and tell them that we need to focus on these very"},{"time":346262,"text":"misunderstood creatures. Volunteer your time"},{"time":349440,"text":"to spread the word. Spread the word."},{"time":352056,"text":"When you walk out of this room, you will be informed"},{"time":354400,"text":"about vultures, but speak to your families, to your children,"},{"time":357200,"text":"to your neighbors about vultures."}]},{"cues":[{"time":359361,"text":"They are very graceful. Charles Darwin said"},{"time":362424,"text":"he changed his mind because he watched them fly"},{"time":365453,"text":"effortlessly without energy in the skies."},{"time":368718,"text":"Kenya, this world, will be much poorer"},{"time":371597,"text":"without these wonderful species."},{"time":374182,"text":"Thank you very much. (Applause)"}]}]}